properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 6 at 7:34PM MST until February 8 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...MAJOR SNOW STORM WILL IMPACT AREAS ALONG AND WEST OF THE
LARAMIE RANGE THROUGH SATURDAY MORNING...

* WHAT...Heavy snow. Additional snow accumulations of 3 to 5
inches. Storm total accumulations of 5 to 8 inches. Winds
gusting as high as 40 mph.

* WHERE...Eastern foothills of the south Laramie Range...including
the towns of Whitaker...Federal and Horse Creek.

* WHEN...Until 5 AM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be hazardous due to icy, snow covered
roads and periods of low visibility in falling snow.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM MST SATURDAY
